<!-- ABOUT CONTENT -->
<section class="pillars-section">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="section-label">Who We Are</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">Built by Black Denisonians, for Black Denisonians</h2>
  </div>

  <div style="max-width:720px;margin-bottom:52px">
    <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.85;color:#444;margin-bottom:20px">The Black Alumni Association of Denison University was founded to create a permanent home for Black graduates — a place where we could stay connected, invest in the next generation, and hold the institution accountable to its commitments.</p>
    <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.85;color:#444;margin-bottom:20px">We are not a social club. We are an organized body with governance, committees, and a growing financial infrastructure. We operate independently while maintaining a productive relationship with Denison University.</p>
    <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.85;color:#444;margin-bottom:20px">Our current priorities: building a sustainable scholarship fund through a Donor-Advised Fund, expanding our alumni network, and launching communications infrastructure — including this newsletter — that keep our community informed and engaged.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="pillars">
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-num">01</div>
      <h3>Independence</h3>
      <p>We govern ourselves. Our scholarship fund sits in a Donor-Advised Fund we control — not in Denison's general endowment. We are a partner, not a subsidiary.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-num">02</div>
      <h3>Accountability</h3>
      <p>We hold Denison to its stated commitments to Black students and the Black community — and we hold ourselves to the same standard.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="pillar">
      <div class="pillar-num">03</div>
      <h3>Legacy</h3>
      <p>Everything we build is designed to outlast us — governance documents, financial infrastructure, and institutional memory that transfers from one generation to the next.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

